  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: How Lonely Sits the City'
      title: How Lonely Sits the City
      number: 1
      content: '    How lonely sits the citythat was full of people!How like a widow
        has she become,she who was great among the nations!She who was a princess
        among the provinceshas become a slave.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  She weeps bitterly in the night,with tears on her cheeks;  among
        all her loversshe has none to comfort her;  all her friends have dealt treacherously
        with her;they have become her enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Judah has gone into exile because of affliction[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        hard servitude;  she dwells now among the nations,  but finds no resting
        place;her pursuers have all overtaken herin the midst of her distress.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The roads to Zion mourn,for none come to the festival;  all her gates
        are desolate;her priests groan;her virgins have been afflicted,[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        she herself suffers bitterly.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:4 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Old Latin '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Her foes have become the head;her enemies prosper,because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has afflicted her  for the multitude of her transgressions;  her children
        have gone away,captives before the foe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'From the daughter of Zionall her majesty has departed.Her princes
        have become like deer  that find no pasture;they fled without strengthbefore
        the pursuer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Jerusalem remembersin the days of her affliction and wandering  all
        the precious thingsthat were hers from days of old.When her people fell into
        the hand of the foe,and there was none to help her,her foes gloated over
        her;they mocked at her downfall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Jerusalem sinned grievously;therefore she became filthy;all who
        honored her despise her,  for they have seen her nakedness;she herself groansand
        turns her face away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Her uncleanness was in her skirts;  she took no thought of her future;[[COMMENT(0)]]therefore
        her fall is terrible;  she has no comforter.\u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        behold my affliction,for the enemy has triumphed!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The enemy has stretched out his handsover all her precious things;for
        she has seen the nationsenter her sanctuary,those whom you forbadeto enter
        your congregation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "All her people groanas they search for bread;they trade their treasures
        for foodto revive their strength.\u201CLook, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and see,for I am despised.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIs it nothing to you, all you who pass by?  Look and seeif
        there is any sorrow like my sorrow,which was brought upon me,which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        inflictedon the day of his fierce anger.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CFrom on high he sent fire;into my bones[[COMMENT(0)]] he made
        it descend;  he spread a net for my feet;he turned me back;  he has left
        me stunned,faint all the day long.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:13 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CMy transgressions were bound[[COMMENT(0)]] into a yoke;by his
        hand they were fastened together;they were set upon my neck;he caused my
        strength to fail;the Lord gave me into the handsof those whom I cannot withstand.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:14 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThe Lord rejectedall my mighty men in my midst;he summoned
        an assembly against meto crush my young men;  the Lord has trodden as in
        a winepressthe virgin daughter of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CFor these things I weep;my eyes flow with tears;for a comforter
        is far from me,one to revive my spirit;my children are desolate,for the enemy
        has prevailed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Zion stretches out her hands,but there is none to comfort her;the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has commanded against Jacobthat his neighbors
        should be his foes;Jerusalem has becomea filthy thing among them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is in the right,  for I have
        rebelled against his word;but hear, all you peoples,and see my suffering; 
        my young women and my young menhave gone into captivity.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CI called to my lovers,but they deceived me;my priests and eldersperished
        in the city,while they sought foodto revive their strength.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CLook, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for I am in distress; 
        my stomach churns;my heart is wrung within me,because I have been very rebellious. 
        In the street the sword bereaves;in the house it is like death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThey heard[[COMMENT(0)]]  my groaning,yet there is no one to
        comfort me.All my enemies have heard of my trouble;  they are glad that you
        have done it.You have brought the day you announced;  now let them be as
        I am.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:21 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac Syriac '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  \u201CLet all their evildoing come before you,and deal with themas
        you have dealt with mebecause of all my transgressions;for my groans are
        many,and my heart is faint.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Lord Has Destroyed Without Pity'
      title: The Lord Has Destroyed Without Pity
      number: 1
      content: '  How the Lord in his angerhas set the daughter of Zion under a cloud! 
        He has cast down from heaven to earththe splendor of Israel;he has not remembered
        his footstoolin the day of his anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord has swallowed up without mercyall the habitations of Jacob;in
        his wrath he has broken downthe strongholds of the daughter of Judah;he has
        brought down to the ground in dishonorthe kingdom and its rulers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He has cut down in fierce angerall the might of Israel;  he has withdrawn
        from them his right handin the face of the enemy;  he has burned like a flaming
        fire in Jacob,consuming all around.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  He has bent his bow like an enemy,with his right hand set like
        a foe;and he has killed all who were delightful in our eyesin the tent of
        the daughter of Zion;he has poured out his fury like fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  The Lord has become like an enemy;  he has swallowed up Israel; 
        he has swallowed up all its palaces;he has laid in ruins its strongholds,and
        he has multiplied in the daughter of Judah  mourning and lamentation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He has laid waste his booth like a garden,laid in ruins his meeting
        place;  the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has made Zion forgetfestival and
        Sabbath,and in his fierce indignation has spurned king and priest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The Lord has scorned his altar,  disowned his sanctuary;  he has
        delivered into the hand of the enemythe walls of her palaces;  they raised
        a clamor in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>as on the day of
        festival.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> determined to lay in ruins  the
        wall of the daughter of Zion;  he stretched out the measuring line;he did
        not restrain his hand from destroying;  he caused rampart and wall to lament; 
        they languished together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Her gates have sunk into the ground;  he has ruined and broken her
        bars;  her king and princes are among the nations;the law is no more,and
        her prophets findno vision from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The elders of the daughter of Zion  sit on the ground in silence; 
        they have thrown dust on their headsand put on sackcloth;the young women
        of Jerusalemhave bowed their heads to the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  My eyes are spent with weeping;  my stomach churns;  my bile is
        poured out to the ground  because of the destruction of the daughter of my
        people,  because infants and babies faintin the streets of the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They cry to their mothers,  \u201CWhere is bread and wine?\u201D 
        as they faint like a wounded manin the streets of the city,as their life
        is poured outon their mothers\u2019 bosom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'What can I say for you, to what compare you,O daughter of Jerusalem? 
        What can I liken to you, that I may comfort you,O virgin daughter of Zion? 
        For your ruin is vast as the sea;who can heal you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Your prophets have seen for youfalse and deceptive visions;  they
        have not exposed your iniquityto restore your fortunes,  but have seen for
        you oraclesthat are false and misleading.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "All who pass along the wayclap their hands at you;  they hiss and
        wag their headsat the daughter of Jerusalem:\u201CIs this the city that was
        called  the perfection of beauty,  the joy of all the earth?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  All your enemiesrail against you;they hiss, they gnash their teeth,they
        cry: \u201CWe have swallowed her!Ah, this is the day we longed for;now we
        have it; we see it!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has done what he purposed;he has
        carried out his word,which he commanded long ago;  he has thrown down without
        pity;  he has made the enemy rejoice over youand exalted the might of your
        foes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Their heart cried to the Lord.O wall of the daughter of Zion,  let
        tears stream down like a torrent  day and night!  Give yourself no rest, 
        your eyes no respite!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CArise, cry out in the night,at the beginning of the night watches! 
        Pour out your heart like waterbefore the presence of the Lord!  Lift your
        hands to himfor the lives of your children,  who faint for hungerat the head
        of every street.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Look, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and see!  With whom have you
        dealt thus?  Should women eat the fruit of their womb,the children of their
        tender care?Should priest and prophet be killedin the sanctuary of the Lord?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'In the dust of the streets  lie the young and the old;  my young
        women and my young menhave fallen by the sword;  you have killed them in
        the day of your anger,slaughtering without pity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: You summoned as if to a festival day  my terrors on every side,  and
        on the day of the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>no one escaped
        or survived;  those whom I held and raisedmy enemy destroyed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Great Is Your Faithfulness'
      title: Great Is Your Faithfulness
      number: 1
      content: '    I am the man who has seen afflictionunder the rod of his wrath;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'he has driven and brought me  into darkness without any light;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'surely against me he turns his handagain and again the whole day
        long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He has made my flesh and my skin waste away;  he has broken my bones;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  he has besieged and enveloped mewith bitterness and tribulation;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  he has made me dwell in darknesslike the dead of long ago.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  He has walled me about so that I cannot escape;he has made my chains
        heavy;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'though I call and cry for help,he shuts out my prayer;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  he has blocked my ways with blocks of stones;he has made my paths
        crooked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  He is a bear lying in wait for me,a lion in hiding;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  he turned aside my steps and tore me to pieces;  he has made me
        desolate;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  he bent his bow and set meas a target for his arrow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He drove into my kidneys  the arrows of his quiver;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  I have become the laughingstock of all peoples,  the object of
        their taunts all day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  He has filled me with bitterness;he has sated me with wormwood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  He has made my teeth grind on gravel,and made me cower in ashes;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'my soul is bereft of peace;I have forgotten what happiness[[COMMENT(0)]]
        is;  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  so I say, \u201CMy endurance has perished;so has my hope from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Remember my affliction and my wanderings,  the wormwood and the
        gall!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My soul continually remembers it  and is bowed down within me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But this I call to mind,and therefore I have hope:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  The steadfast love of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> never ceases;[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        his mercies never come to an end;  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:22 '
        content: Syriac, Targum; Hebrew <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'they are new every morning;  great is your faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is my portion,\u201D says
        my soul,  \u201Ctherefore I will hope in him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is good to those who wait for him,to
        the soul who seeks him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  It is good that one should wait quietlyfor the salvation of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  It is good for a man that he bearthe yoke in his youth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Let him sit alone in silencewhen it is laid on him;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  let him put his mouth in the dust\u2014there may yet be hope;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  let him give his cheek to the one who strikes,and let him be filled
        with insults.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  For the Lord will notcast off forever,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'but, though he cause grief, he will have compassion  according to
        the abundance of his steadfast love;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '  for he does not afflict from his heartor grieve the children of
        men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'To crush underfootall the prisoners of the earth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '  to deny a man justicein the presence of the Most High,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'to subvert a man in his lawsuit,  the Lord does not approve.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '  Who has spoken and it came to pass,unless the Lord has commanded
        it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '  Is it not from the mouth of the Most Highthat good and bad come?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '  Why should a living man complain,a man, about the punishment of
        his sins?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Let us test and examine our ways,  and return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: '  Let us lift up our hearts and handsto God in heaven:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "  \u201CWe have transgressed and rebelled,and you have not forgiven.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "\u201CYou have wrapped yourself with anger and pursued us,  killing
        without pity;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '  you have wrapped yourself with a cloudso that no prayer can pass
        through.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: '  You have made us scum and garbageamong the peoples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "  \u201CAll our enemiesopen their mouths against us;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: '  panic and pitfall have come upon us,devastation and destruction;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: '  my eyes flow with rivers of tearsbecause of the destruction of
        the daughter of my people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "  \u201CMy eyes will flow without ceasing,without respite,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: '  until the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> from heavenlooks down and
        sees;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'my eyes cause me griefat the fate of all the daughters of my city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "  \u201CI have been hunted like a birdby those who were my enemies
        without cause;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: '  they flung me alive into the pit  and cast stones on me;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "  water closed over my head;I said, \u2018I am lost.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "  \u201CI called on your name, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,from
        the depths of the pit;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "  you heard my plea, \u2018Do not closeyour ear to my cry for help!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "  You came near when I called on you;you said, \u2018Do not fear!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "\u201CYou have taken up my cause, O Lord;you have redeemed my life.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'You have seen the wrong done to me, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;judge
        my cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'You have seen all their vengeance,all their plots against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "  \u201CYou have heard their taunts, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,all
        their plots against me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'The lips and thoughts of my assailantsare against me all the day
        long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: '  Behold their sitting and their rising;  I am the object of their
        taunts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "  \u201CYou will repay them,[[COMMENT(0)]] O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        according to the work of their hands.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:64 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'You will give them[[COMMENT(0)]] dullness of heart;your curse will
        be on them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:65 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: "You will pursue them[[COMMENT(0)]] in anger and destroy themfrom
        under your heavens, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '3:66 '
        content: 'Or Syriac (compare Septuagint, Vulgate); Hebrew <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Holy Stones Lie Scattered'
      title: The Holy Stones Lie Scattered
      number: 1
      content: '    How the gold has grown dim,how the pure gold is changed!The holy
        stones lie scattered  at the head of every street.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The precious sons of Zion,worth their weight in fine gold,how they
        are regarded as earthen pots,the work of a potter\u2019s hands!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Even jackals offer the breast;they nurse their young;but the daughter
        of my people has become cruel,like the ostriches in the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The tongue of the nursing infant sticksto the roof of its mouth for
        thirst;  the children beg for food,but no one gives to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Those who once feasted on delicaciesperish in the streets;  those
        who were brought up in purpleembrace ash heaps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  For the chastisement[[COMMENT(0)]] of the daughter of my people
        has been greaterthan the punishment of Sodom,  which was overthrown in a
        moment,and no hands were wrung for her.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:6 '
        content: Or Or The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Her princes were purer than snow,whiter than milk;their bodies were
        more ruddy than coral,the beauty of their form[[COMMENT(0)]] was like sapphire.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        content: 'The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertainHebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Now their face is blacker than soot;they are not recognized in
        the streets;their skin has shriveled on their bones;it has become as dry
        as wood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Happier were the victims of the swordthan the victims of hunger,who
        wasted away, piercedby lack of the fruits of the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  The hands of compassionate women  have boiled their own children; 
        they became their foodduring the destruction of the daughter of my people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave full vent to his wrath;he
        poured out his hot anger,and he kindled a fire in Zionthat consumed its foundations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  The kings of the earth did not believe,nor any of the inhabitants
        of the world,that foe or enemy could enterthe gates of Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'This was for the sins of her prophetsand the iniquities of her priests,who
        shed in the midst of herthe blood of the righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  They wandered, blind, through the streets;they were so defiled
        with blood  that no one was able to touchtheir garments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAway! Unclean!\u201D people cried at them.\u201CAway! Away!
        Do not touch!\u201DSo they became fugitives and wanderers;people said among
        the nations,\u201CThey shall stay with us no longer.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> himself[[COMMENT(0)]] has scattered
        them;he will regard them no more;  no honor was shown to the priests,  no
        favor to the elders.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Our eyes failed, ever watching  vainly for help;in our watching
        we watchedfor a nation which could not save.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  They dogged our stepsso that we could not walk in our streets; 
        our end drew near; our days were numbered,for our end had come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Our pursuers were swifterthan the eagles in the heavens;they chased
        us on the mountains;they lay in wait for us in the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  The breath of our nostrils, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anointed,was captured in their pits,of whom we said, \u201CUnder his shadowwe
        shall live among the nations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Rejoice and be glad, O daughter of Edom,you who dwell in the land
        of Uz;but to you also the cup shall pass;you shall become drunk and strip
        yourself bare.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  The punishment of your iniquity, O daughter of Zion, is accomplished;he
        will keep you in exile no longer;[[COMMENT(0)]]but your iniquity, O daughter
        of Edom, he will punish;he will uncover your sins.'
      comments:
      - number: '4:22 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Restore Us to Yourself, O '
      title: 'Restore Us to Yourself, O '
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    Remember, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        what has befallen us;look, and see our disgrace!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Our inheritance has been turned over to strangers,our homes to
        foreigners.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'We have become orphans, fatherless;our mothers are like widows.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'We must pay for the water we drink;the wood we get must be bought.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Our pursuers are at our necks;we are weary; we are given no rest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'We have given the hand to Egypt, and to Assyria,to get bread enough.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Our fathers sinned, and are no more;  and we bear their iniquities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Slaves rule over us;there is none to deliver us from their hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  We get our bread at the peril of our lives,because of the sword
        in the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Our skin is hot as an ovenwith the burning heat of famine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Women are raped in Zion,young women in the towns of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Princes are hung up by their hands;  no respect is shown to the
        elders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Young men are compelled to grind at the mill,and boys stagger under
        loads of wood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  The old men have left the city gate,the young men their music.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  The joy of our hearts has ceased;  our dancing has been turned
        to mourning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  The crown has fallen from our head;woe to us, for we have sinned!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For this our heart has become sick,for these things our eyes have
        grown dim,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'for Mount Zion which lies desolate;  jackals prowl over it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  But you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, reign forever;your throne
        endures to all generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Why do you forget us forever,why do you forsake us for so many
        days?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  Restore us to yourself, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that we
        may be restored!Renew our days as of old\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  unless you have utterly rejected us,and you remain exceedingly
        angry with us.'
      comments: []
